            <div type="apparatus" resp="#'JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app loc="1"><note>Manganaro: [Σ?]ι<unclear>μ</unclear>ύλου</note></app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>Manganaro: [Κ]αλλιπίδα</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#JP">
                <p>(tomb) of Simylos son of Kallipidas</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The name Simylos is attested at Tauromenion and Akrai in the Hellenistic period, making it the most likely restoration of the name in line 1 (although one might note that both Κωμύλος (Catania) and Μύλος (Monte Saraceno) are also attested on the island). The piece appears to be part of an epitymbion funerary monument, of a type common in Hellenistic Sicily, including along the north coast of the island (e.g. at Cefalu).</p>
            </div>
